 document five landmark cases, representing the most important organized crime prosecutions of the modern era—Teamsters Local 560, The Pizza Connection, The Commission, the International Teamsters, and the prosecution of John Gotti.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMafia trialszUnited States. 0aMafia trials. 0aOrganized crimezUnited StatesvBibliography. 0aOrganized crime. 0aRacketeeringzUnited States. 0aRacketeering. 7aLAW / Criminal Law / General.2bisacsh1 aPanarella, Christopher.1 aWorthington, Jay.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z97831107169240 cprintz978081474195540uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814743959.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814743959423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814743959/original  a978-3-11-071692-4  New York University Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK